  "_comment": "7-frame holy smite, rigged on the cleric-battle SKELETON (chest root, robe skirt, mace-arm + mace, coif 3/4 head) instead of a slid flat body. The mace lifts overhead on a slow held anticipation while a gold holy glow gathers on its head (the spark scales up), then an EXPLOSIVE single-frame swing brings it down, a held impact key (hold 3) bursts the glow to a bright gold flash as the body lunges into the blow, a one-frame overshoot, and a slow settle. No separate legs (robe skirt), so the weight reads through a hard torso lean that sways the whole robe. Facing right.",
